txt.en: 'As we move throughout Kûr Anzar, be on the look out for supplies. Many valuables and packs have been stolen from residents of Urmâkh, both in the initial fight for Kûr Anzar that saw us expelled and in the time since in Urmâkh.\n\n'Grab any supplies or packs you see. You'll be harming their war efforts and aiding the everyday people of Renewed Hamât.'
Grab Urmâkh supplies in Kur Anzar ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Grab supplies and packs that belong to the innocent residents of Urmâkh as you move through Kûr Anzar.
'This is a wonder. Well done. Every pack not in their possession is food in the bellies and supplies on the shelves of the people of Renewed Hamât. Thank you for this.'
As you liberate Kûr Anzar, recover supplies stolen from Urmâkh along the way.
